rer, Collegeville, PA.[9] Fan-Havard P, Sanchorawala V, Oh J, Moser EM, Smith SP "Concurrent use of foscarnet and ciprofloxacin may increase the propensity for seizures." Ann Pharmacother 28 (1994): 869-72[10] "Product Information. Raxar (grepafloxacin)." Glaxo Wellcome, Research Triangle Park, NC.', 'Tetracycline, Rifamycin, Oxytetracycline, Polymyxin B, Famciclovir, Sulfamethizole, Cefuroxime, Trifluridine, Benzylpenicillin, Ampicillin, Chloramphenicol, More', 'Paritaprevir, Glecaprevir, Tenofovir alafenamide, Maraviroc, Amprenavir, Simeprevir, Zanamivir, Cabotegravir, Lenacapavir, Telaprevir, Velpatasvir, More', 1767369485);
