ssible development of tuberculosis in patients who tested negative for latent tuberculosis infection prior to initiating therapy.', 'Major', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/125117/', '[1] "Product Information. Xeljanz (tofacitinib)." Pfizer U.S. Pharmaceuticals Group, New York, NY.', 'Apremilast, Pirfenidone, Belumosudil, Teprotumumab, Emapalumab, Baricitinib, Tofacitinib, Ravulizumab, Pegcetacoplan, Eculizumab, Sutimlimab', 'Antithymocyte immunoglobulin (rabbit), Tocilizumab, Secukinumab, Anifrolumab, Ravulizumab, Mycophenolic acid, Abatacept, Apremilast, Inebilizumab, Belumosudil, Thalidomide, More', 1767369485);
